<footer class="footer wrap">
  <p>
    Saezuri is an original, clean-room reimplementation of a bird-collage frontend in the
    kachō-e style of
    <a href="https://github.com/Twarner491/AvianVisitors">AvianVisitors</a> by Teddy Warner.
    The illustrations pictured are AvianVisitors artwork, licensed
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/">CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0</a> —
    which builds on <a href="https://github.com/Nachtzuster/BirdNET-Pi">BirdNET-Pi</a> and
    BirdNET from the K. Lisa Yang Center for Conservation Bioacoustics, Cornell Lab of
    Ornithology. Detections come from
    <a href="https://github.com/tphakala/birdnet-go">BirdNET-Go</a>.
  </p>
